{"title": "Unsanitized user input in deserialization method", "summary": "  It is bad practice to deserialize untrusted data, such as data that comes from external sources like user input or request parameters, without sufficient verification. Attackers can transfer payloads or malicious code via serialized data, and deserializing such data puts your application at risk. ", "description": "\n\nIt is bad practice to deserialize untrusted data, such as data that comes\nfrom external sources like user input or request parameters, without sufficient\nverification. Attackers can transfer payloads or malicious code via serialized\ndata, and deserializing such data puts your application at risk.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Do not deserialize untrusted data\n\n\u2705 Validate and sanitize data before attempting to (de)serialize it\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-502"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/go_lang_deserialization_of_user_input", "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Deserialization_Cheat_Sheet.html"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}